Basically AlexNET but with fewer layers and smaller. 
Starts with a slightly larger resolution, as a result of the hyperparameters we chose,
since we didn't want to round down and waste data. It gets around 60% accuracy which isn't too bad.

So far we haven't tried manipulations, this is just a baseline - minimum viable product.